<D>__{because you're scared.}
<A>__{we hear the dull report of a rifle and the deafening sound of shattering glass. the gun shot hits ray in the back, knocking him to the floor. he lies still.}
<B>__{close shot abby}
<A>__{she stares dumbly down at ray. she looks slowly up to the window.}
<B>__{the window}
<A>__{it has a gaping black hole. the sound of shattering glass still reverberates in the apartment. small shards of glass chink down from the window and shatter on the floor.}
<B>__{back to abby}
<A>__{staring at the window, paralyzed almost in a trance. quiet except for the chinking of glass.}
